description: Emily, 22, is a college student studying biology at the University of California, Los Angeles. She is single and lives with her parents, who are middle-income earners. Emily is independent-minded and passionate about environmental conservation.

Fatima, 35, is a small business owner running a local cafe in Chicago. She has a high school diploma and comes from a lower-middle-class background. Fatima is a single parent and juggles the demands of work and raising her two children.

Olivia, 41, is a marketing executive at a tech firm in Seattle. She holds a master's degree and comes from an upper-middle-class family. Olivia is married to her college sweetheart, and they have been trying to conceive for the past year.

Lila, 17, is a high school student in rural Tennessee. She comes from a low-income household and is the first in her family to consider going to college. Lila is in a committed relationship with her boyfriend and is unexpectedly pregnant.

Sophia, 52, is a semi-retired nurse living in Miami. She has a bachelor's degree in nursing and is a widow after her husband passed away five years ago. Sophia is independent and financially stable, but she feels lonely at times.

Amelia, 27, is a barista at a local coffee shop in Portland, Oregon. She has a high school diploma and comes from a working-class family. Amelia is in a domestic partnership with her long-term girlfriend, and they are considering starting a family.

Isabella, 31, is a freelance graphic designer based in New York City. She has a bachelor's degree in fine arts and comes from an upper-class background. Isabella is single and focused on her career, but she occasionally feels the pressure to settle down and have children.

Ava, 24, is a recent college graduate working as a research assistant at a university in Boston. She has a bachelor's degree and comes from a middle-income household. Ava is in a long-term relationship with her boyfriend, and they are discussing the possibility of marriage and starting a family.

Mia, 45, is a high school English teacher in a small town in Kansas. She has a master's degree in education and comes from a lower-middle-class family. Mia is divorced and a single parent to two teenage daughters, and she is considering adopting a child.

Harper, 19, is a first-year college student at a community college in Los Angeles. She comes from a low-income household and is the first in her family to attend college. Harper is in a casual relationship with her boyfriend and is unsure about her future plans.
